history.text: Hello
Frozen sounds like a great movie. It's a Disney animated musical and has high ratings from critics.
I haven't seen the movie. I really want to see it though.

Have you heard the music? Idina Menzel sings th
e part of Elsa.
Maybe I have. Is Elsa the main character?
Elsa is one of the main cast members. The others are Anna, her younger sister, and Kristoff, an iceman.
I think I've seen Kristoff. What country does the movie take place in?
A kingdom called Arendelle
Is that a ficitonal country?

It is a fantasy film 
based on a fairy tale
Nice. What year did the movie debut?
Are they going to make a sequel?
I don't know. One of the critics said it was destined for a Broadway show!
That makes sense if it is that good. What is the moral of the movie?
I'd say it's about mastering your powers rather than trying to suppress them.
That resonates with me. I really want to see the movie now.
If you like musical fantasy and princesses, I think you'd find a lot there.
I agree.
There is also a colony of magical trolls, which sounds cool.
Sounds interesting.
And it's Disney's 53rd animated feature film! They must be doing something right.
Wow! 53. They are doing something right!
There are actors in this film who play characters at different ages. I wonder if they are trying to broaden their appeal.
They probably are. They don't want to be type-cast.
I can understand that. I hate to tell you spoilers, but in this one the handsome prince turns out to be a bad guy!
Really? That is surprising in a Disney movie.
The directors are Chris Buck and Jennifer Lee, I guess maybe they wanted something different
I haven't heard of them. But if you say it is a good movie, they must be doing something right.

uid2response.feedback: It was a very smooth conversation. The document didn't have all the information I might have wanted but it was useful and would have been useful even if I hadn't seen the movie.
